WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:02.240 --> 00:00:03.240
Hello.

00:00:03.240 --> 00:00:08.800
I wanted to speak to you to make sure
you are aware of the latest updates on UAlbany’s

00:00:08.800 --> 00:00:11.650
response to COVID-19.

00:00:11.650 --> 00:00:17.330
This is a fast-moving situation, and frequent
updates are necessary.

00:00:17.330 --> 00:00:23.880
Yesterday, you received an email from me explaining
that after spring break, on March 23, all

00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:27.500
UAlbany classes will be delivered remotely.

00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:33.160
This morning, you received notice that we
suspended classes today, Thursday.

00:00:33.160 --> 00:00:39.620
This was done as precaution after we learned
of a confirmed case of COVID-19 in our campus

00:00:39.620 --> 00:00:41.570
community.

00:00:41.570 --> 00:00:45.580
This individual will remain isolated from
the campus population until they have been

00:00:45.580 --> 00:00:48.890
cleared by public health officials.

00:00:48.890 --> 00:00:54.150
We are working closely with the Albany County
Department of Health to reach out to any student,

00:00:54.150 --> 00:00:59.760
faculty or staff member who may have come
in contact with this individual.

00:00:59.760 --> 00:01:05.760
Also as a precaution, we have closed the business
building today for cleaning.

00:01:05.760 --> 00:01:11.079
As I said, these fast-changing circumstances
are going to continue to require frequent

00:01:11.079 --> 00:01:12.079
updates.

00:01:12.079 --> 00:01:18.820
It is very important that you continue to
monitor your e-mail for updates today, tomorrow

00:01:18.820 --> 00:01:21.780
and throughout spring break.

00:01:21.780 --> 00:01:27.999
Please exercise caution regarding information
you may see about the virus on social media,

00:01:27.999 --> 00:01:31.649
especially as it relates to our campus community.

00:01:31.649 --> 00:01:38.689
Our county and state health departments provide
the only official confirmation of any communicable

00:01:38.689 --> 00:01:42.820
disease, including COVID-19.

00:01:42.820 --> 00:01:49.530
For additional information, visit the COVID-19
information page on our website.

00:01:49.530 --> 00:01:54.870
For those of you who are leaving for spring
break, please travel safely.

00:01:54.870 --> 00:02:00.109
And everyone, please continue to follow proper
safety protocols:

00:02:00.109 --> 00:02:07.709
Wash your hands frequently, use hand sanitizer,
cough and sneeze into your elbow or sleeve,

00:02:07.709 --> 00:02:14.440
avoid large gatherings, stay home if you are
sick, and maintain as much social distance

00:02:14.440 --> 00:02:16.700
as possible.

00:02:16.700 --> 00:02:23.030
Let us continue to make sure that all members
of our community are treated with the care,

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:27.750
dignity and respect that we all deserve.

00:02:27.750 --> 00:02:36.840
Be safe, be well, stay healthy… and again,
please watch your emails, texts, and the official

00:02:36.840 --> 00:02:41.830
UAlbany social media channels for ongoing
updates.

00:02:41.830 --> 00:02:45.590
As the Great Dane family, we will get through
this together!

00:02:45.590 --> 00:02:47.500
Muchísimas gracias!

